    title: "Class Fields At Top",
    summary: "Class fields must be declared before constructors and methods, with no blank lines between them.",
    markdown:
      "# class-fields-at-top\n\nClass fields must be declared before constructors and methods, with no blank lines between them.\n\n## Bad\n\n```typescript\nclass UserService {\n  public getName() { return this.name; }\n  private name: string;\n  private age: number;\n}\n```\n\n## Good\n\n```typescript\nclass UserService {\n  private name: string;\n  private age: number;\n\n  public getName() { return this.name; }\n}\n```\n\n## Why\n\nGrouping all fields at the top of the class lets readers quickly inventory class state without scanning the entire body.",
