    summary: "Do not instantiate the built-in `Error` class directly.",
    markdown:
      "# no-new-error\n\nDo not instantiate the built-in `Error` class directly.\n\n## Bad\n\n```typescript\nthrow new Error('something went wrong');\n```\n\n## Good\n\n```typescript\nimport { ValidationError } from './errors';\n\nthrow new ValidationError('invalid input');\n```\n\n## Why\n\nGeneric errors lack context and type information. Custom error classes enable structured error handling and make catch blocks meaningful.",
    ruleSourcePath: "packages/guardrails/src/rules/no-new-error/rule.ts",
    docsSourcePath: "packages/guardrails/src/rules/no-new-error/docs.md",
