    title: "String Mapping",
    summary: "Ensure a set of source files has matching marker strings in another set of files.",
    markdown:
      '# string-mapping\n\nEnsure a set of source files has matching marker strings in another set of files.\n\n```json\n{\n  "@rule/string-mapping": {\n    "cases": [\n      {\n        "source": {\n          "type": "files-like",\n          "files": "src/operations/*.ts"\n        },\n        "matches": {\n          "type": "strings-like",\n          "files": "src/testing/*.ts",\n          "pattern": "describe(\'Operation: $1\'"\n        }\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n}\n```\n\nPlaceholders:\n\n- `$0`: source file path relative to the package root\n- `$1`: source file basename without extension\n- `$2`: source filename with extension',
    ruleSourcePath: "packages/guardrails/src/rules/string-mapping/rule.ts",
    docsSourcePath: "packages/guardrails/src/rules/string-mapping/docs.md",
