    markdown:
      '## What It Includes\n\nGuardrails TypeScript bundles 47 related rules into one opt-in group.\n\n## Enable This Group\n\n```json\n{\n  "inherit": "@group/guardrails-typescript"\n}\n```\n\n## Included Rules\n\n- `class-fields-at-top` - Class fields must be declared before constructors and methods, with no blank lines between them.\n- `class-file-name-matches-class` - Files that define a top-level class must use the kebab-case form of the class name as the filename.\n- `class-owns-utilities` - Files that define a class must not also define top-level constants or functions.\n- `export-classes` - Classes must be exported directly from the module at the top level.\n- `no-local-contracts-in-pure-class-files` - Files that export a class must not define local types or interfaces.\n- `pure-class-exports` - Files that export a class must export only that class.\n- `require-class-jsdoc` - Every class must have a JSDoc block comment.\n- `require-public-method-comments` - All public class methods must have a comment above them.\n- `no-single-line-block-comments` - Block comments (`/** ... */`) must span multiple lines.\n- `max-indent-depth` - Non-test TypeScript source must not indent beyond 8 levels.\n- `path-names-kebab-case` - Requires TypeScript file and folder names to stay lowercase and use hyphens instead of underscores.\n- `pure-contract-files` - `types.ts` files must contain only imports, exports, interfaces, and type aliases.\n- `pure-index-files` - `index.ts` files must contain only import and export declarations.\n- `pure-tsx-files` - TSX files must define and export only one top-level function.\n- `pure-utils-folders` - Utils folders must be flat (no subdirectories), contain only TypeScript files, and each file must export exactly one function.\n- `reserved-contract-file-names` - Only files named exactly `types.ts` may contain "types" in the file name.\n- `no-complex-parameters` - Parameter types must use simple named types, not inline unions, intersections, tuples, arrays, object literals, or function signatures.\n- `no-complex-returns` - Return types must use simple named types, not inline unions, intersections, tuples, arrays, object literals, or function signatures.\n- `no-function-constructor-overloads` - Multiple function or constructor overload signatures are not allowed.\n- `no-object-destructuring-parameters` - Function and class parameters must not use object destructuring.\n- `no-dynamic-imports` - Disallows dynamic `import()` calls and inline import type queries inside TypeScript source files.\n- `no-exec-sync` - `execSync` is banned. All shell execution must be async.\n- `no-import-meta-url` - `import.meta.url` is not allowed.\n- `no-import-target-extensions` - Import and export specifiers must not end with `.js` or `.ts`.\n- `no-banned-as-casts` - Type assertions using `as any`, `as unknown`, or `as never` are not allowed.\n- `no-global-this` - Do not use `globalThis` to mutate or read globals.\n- `no-inline-await` - Await expressions must be assigned to a variable or used as standalone statements, not inlined into other expressions.\n- `no-mixed-logical-operators-in-if` - If statements must not mix `&&` and `||` in the same condition.\n- `no-new-error` - Do not instantiate the built-in `Error` class directly.\n- `no-object-assign` - `Object.assign(...)` is not allowed.\n- `no-satisfies-keyword` - The TypeScript `satisfies` keyword is not allowed.\n- `test-block-format`\n- `test-name-prefixes`\n- `max-test-assertions` - Each `it(...)` block must contain exactly one `expect(...)` or `assert(...)` call.\n- `max-test-it-block-lines` - Each `it(...)` block must stay at twelve non-comment lines or fewer.\n- `no-nested-describe-blocks` - Nested `describe(...)` blocks are not allowed.\n- `no-vi-mock` - `vi.mock(...)` is not allowed in test files.\n- `snapshot-tests-use-file-snapshots` - Snapshot tests must use `.toMatchFileSnapshot(\'./snapshots/...\')` instead of `.toMatchSnapshot()`.\n- `test-files-use-vitest` - Test files must use Vitest instead of Node built-in testing modules.\n- `pure-test-files` - Test files must only contain imports and `describe(...)` blocks at the top level, and describe blocks must contain only `it(...)` calls.\n- `no-vitest-config-overrides` - `coverage.exclude` and `passWithNoTests: true` are not allowed in vitest config files.\n- `package-errors-file` - Each package\'s `src/errors.ts` must export at least one custom error class that extends Error.\n- `package-readme-md` - Requires every package to ship a sidecar `README.md` next to its `package.json`.\n- `throw-package-errors` - Throw statements must construct a custom error imported from the package\'s `errors.ts` file.\n- `types-only-in-types-files` - Files that only export types and interfaces must be named `types.ts`.\n- `prefer-md-extension` - Disallows the `.markdown` file extension and requires `.md` instead.\n- `code-structure` - Enforces that directories matching a pattern contain all required files or folders.',
